About
See more than 2,000 animals, including sharks, giant rays, endangered green sea turtles, piranha and a Komodo dragon. This unique exhibit gives you the chance to dive with a higher concentration of exotic sharks than you'd ever find in the wild. Last admission at 7:00 PM.
Duration: 1-2 hours
Meets animal welfare guidelines

    Our only complaint was that we wished there was more and the length of the walk to get to it! Loved the exhibits, especially the jellyfish, lionfish and sharks! The staff was wonderful; free wheelchairs are available for those with mobility issues (like me); and the price was beyond reasonable by Las Vegas standards.   • 01DayTripper

    Worth the price of admission.
    The Aquarium was well kept and clean. For the admission price (Adults $30), there was a good variety of exhibits. Reptiles, fish, rays, jellyfish and sharks. It is located in the back of Mandalay Bay convention center and requires a long walk from the front.

  • Quiggles
    Havre, Montana14 contributions
    Visit the ocean floor...
    I have a kid who is obsessed with sharks, so we had to go. There were 2 tunnels - everything swims around you - that was pretty neat. There is a place where you can touch some little rays. There is an employee there to answer questions and direct the contact. They give the rays a "no touch" break every so often. While they are on their break, you can wander around an look at the jellyfish or octopus. There is a big observation type room with glass in the ceiling and floor. There were walls of glass - so you're basically on the ocean floor watching. Our only "complaint" would be that we wish it was bigger. It was August, so it was still hot and a little muggy in there, but absolutely would recommend!
    Visited August 2024
    Traveled with family
    Written August 24, 2024

Beautiful but OVERPRICED!
Very nice exhibits with great sharks, sea turtles, jelly fish, mana rays, a Komodo dragon, an octopus and more. I loved the tunnels and the beautifully planned ship wreck and ancient ruins that make up the exhibits. Why I give them 3 stars? The price! It takes about 40 minutes to walk through, if you take your time and definitely not worth the $30 per person. Luckily we had comp tickets from playing Pop Slots and we were staying in the hotel so no extra fee for parking and we got in free. Otherwise it would have definitely been way over priced!

Stevie Y
8 contributions
Loved the sea turtles
Oct 2024 Couples
Shark Reef at Mandalay Bay offers a unique and well-kept experience, showcasing underwater animals that you dont encounter every day. While the admission can be a bit pricey for the relatively quick tour, the highlight was definitely seeing the massive turtles and having the chance to touch the sting rays.

The staff here are extremely friendly and knowledgeable, enhancing the overall experience with their insights about the exhibits. We redeemed our myVEGAS credits, making it feel worth it, but Im not sure Id pay the full $30 for entry. Overall, its a cool stop for marine life enthusiasts, but be prepared for a brief visit.
